To install

1. Create a database, and read the "setup.sql" file in to it.
2. Edit the includes/global.php settings to your liking.
3. Push on to a php enabled webserver.
4. Open a webbrowser to the "yoursite.com/clean.php" page, this will
   setup a user with the same username and password as your database.
  
5. Logon and add some categories/posts.
6. Set up a script to do a fetch on the yoursite.com/clean.php page 
   daily, this function cleans out the database of old listings etc.
7. Publish your website.
